    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="347" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Dayton</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 258.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 21, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of November 6 (No. 220) has
                            been received.</p>
                <p>The President is very well satisfied with the explanations Mr. Drouyn de
                            l’Huys has given to you of the views of the Emperor in regard to
                            American affairs. The exposition of the views of this government, which
                            you gave to the minister for foreign affairs in return, is approved. You
                            may communicate to him the substance of this despatch.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William L. Dayton</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
